paragraph.content:
in the case of ships registered outside Hong Kong the date of entry
                        into force of the International Regulations for the State whose flag the
                        ship is entitled to fly;

subsection.leadIn:
A vessel other than a crossing vessel or a vessel joining or leaving a lane
                    shall not normally enter a separation zone or cross a separation line
                    except:

paragraph.content:
when
                        both have the wind on the same side, the vessel which is to windward shall
                        keep out of the way of the vessel which is to leeward;

A WIG craft when taking-off, landing and in flight near the surface
                        shall keep well clear of all other vessels and avoid impeding their
                        navigation;

subsection.content:
—a
                    masthead light, 5 miles; except that where the length of the vessel is less than
                    20 m, 3 miles;

paragraph.content:
a second masthead light abaft of and higher than the forward one;
                        except that a vessel of less than 50 m in length shall not be obliged to
                        exhibit such light but may do so;

A power-driven vessel of less than 12 m in length may in lieu of the
                        lights prescribed in paragraph (a) of this Rule exhibit an all-round white
                        light and sidelights;

if it is less than 25 m in breadth, one all-round white light at or
                        near the forward end and one at or near the after end except that dracones
                        need not exhibit a light at or near the forward end;

if it exceeds 100 m in length, additional all-round white lights
                        between the lights prescribed in subparagraphs (i) and (ii) so that the
                        distance between the lights shall not exceed 100 m;

a masthead light abaft of and higher than the all-round green light; a
                        vessel of less than 50 m in length shall not be obliged to exhibit such a
                        light but may do so;

when there is outlying gear extending more than 150 m horizontally from
                        the vessel, an all-round white light or a cone apex upwards in the direction
                        of the gear;

3 all-round lights in a vertical line where they can best be seen. The
                        highest and lowest of these lights shall be red and the middle light shall
                        be white;

3 shapes in a vertical line where they can best be seen. The highest
                        and lowest of these shapes shall be balls and the middle one a
                        diamond;

when making way through the water, a masthead light or lights,
                        sidelights and a sternlight, in addition to the lights prescribed in
                        subparagraph (i);

3 all-round lights in a vertical line where they can best be seen. The
                        highest and lowest of these lights shall be red and the middle light shall
                        be white;

the duration of each flash shall be about one second, the interval
                        between flashes shall be about one second, and the interval between
                        successive signals shall be not less than 10 seconds;

—2
                        prolonged blasts followed by one short blast to mean “I intend to overtake
                        you on your starboard side”;

—2
                        prolonged blasts followed by 2 short blasts to mean “I intend to overtake
                        you on your port side”;

subsection.content:
a signal sent by radiotelephony consisting of the spoken word “MAYDAY”;
                    (L.N. 53 of
                    2016)
